# Pseudo column is false column which is presented in each and every table, but we have to call it explicitly
# We have two types of pseudo column and they are
1. RowId
2. RowNum

1. RowId
* RowId is 18 digits hexadecimal number
* It is static
* We can't modify or update or delete the RowId
* RowId is created at the time of insertion
* We can access the records using RowId very fast
* By using RowId we can access the duplicate records also.
E.g.,
SELECT ROWID, EMP.*
FROM EMP;

2. RowNum
* RowNum is used to assign serial number at the time of execution
* It is dynamic
* RowNum is started with 1 and get incremented by one (1)
E.g.,
SELECT ROWNUM, EMP.*
FROM EMP;

# First half record from emp table
SELECT * FROM (SELECT ROWNUM AS SLNO, EMP.*
               FROM EMP)
WHERE SLNO<=(SELECT COUNT(*)/2 FROM EMP);

# Second half records from emp table
SELECT * FROM(SELECT ROWNUM AS SLNO, EMP.*
               FROM EMP)
WHERE SLNO>(SELECT COUNT(*)/2 FROM EMP);
